I"„<p>RSA was first publicly described by Ron Rivest, Adi Shamir, and Leonard Adleman in 1977.  As a highly secure and reliable asymmetrical cryptosystem, it plays an essential role in peopleâ€™s daily use of the internet. Examples include RSA digital signature and certificate, TLS, SSL, etc.</p>

<p>Similar to the Diffie-Hellman protocol, the RSA makes good use of the modulo exponential because it is a one-way function that is easy to do in one direction but hard to reverse in the other.  Eulerâ€™s totient function is used to construct a big prime with known prime factors, and the public and private keys are generated based on them.</p>

